00:19:37.802 --> 00:19:40.387
- Mm.
- And that's super far away.

492
00:19:40.388 --> 00:19:42.347
And I was scared
that all of the other kids

493
00:19:42.348 --> 00:19:43.723
were gonna be smarter
than I was.

494
00:19:43.724 --> 00:19:46.184
- Mm-hmm.
- So. I chose Georgia.

495
00:19:46.185 --> 00:19:48.520
One morning. my dad
plops two tickets into my lap

496
00:19:48.521 --> 00:19:50.689
nonstop to Providence.
Rhode Island.

497
00:19:50.690 --> 00:19:52.440
Neither of us
had been out of the state.

498
00:19:52.441 --> 00:19:55.652
and I was just super excited
to go on a trip. so off we went.

499
00:19:55.653 --> 00:19:58.697
Yeah. we traveled all the time
when Katie was a kid.

500
00:19:58.698 --> 00:20:01.366
She's been everywhere.
She loved Prague.

501
00:20:01.367 --> 00:20:04.035
She used to call it "Pwag."

502
00:20:04.036 --> 00:20:06.162
- You weren't done. were you?
- When we got to Providence...

503
00:20:06.163 --> 00:20:09.416
- Okay.
- ...instantly. I knew I had to go to Brown.

504
00:20:09.417 --> 00:20:11.167
And so. I did.

505
00:20:11.168 --> 00:20:13.837
- Hmm.
- Be like my dad.

506
00:20:13.838 --> 00:20:15.213
Find a way in.

507
00:20:15.214 --> 00:20:16.673
<i>Doesn't matter what it is.</i>

508
00:20:16.674 --> 00:20:18.676
<i>just something to let
her know you give a shit.</i>

509
00:20:29.186 --> 00:20:32.689
Come on. Come on.
Come on.

510
00:20:35.359 --> 00:20:38.403
What am I doing?
This is stupid.

511
00:20:38.404 --> 00:20:40.029
Oh. Come on.

512
00:20:41.615 --> 00:20:42.741
No. no. no. no. no. no!

513
00:20:45.745 --> 00:20:47.121
I got it!

514
00:20:48.038 --> 00:20:49.372
- Ouch!
- Okay. quit squirming.

515
00:20:49.373 --> 00:20:51.624
- I'm almost done.
- God.

516
00:20:51.625 --> 00:20:54.961
Katie burned all my clothes.
she punched me in the eye.

517
00:20:54.962 --> 00:20:56.546
and I'm the one who's
gonna look like an idiot

518
00:20:56.547 --> 00:20:58.840
in front of millions of people.
It's just not fair.

519
00:20:58.841 --> 00:21:00.259
So. Katie did that?

520
00:21:02.303 --> 00:21:03.720
You didn't tell me.

521
00:21:03.721 --> 00:21:06.222
Yeah. yeah. yes.
Okay. yes. fine.

522
00:21:06.223 --> 00:21:07.599
She did it. yes.

523
00:21:07.600 --> 00:21:09.726
And this whole thing
is such a bloody mess.

524
00:21:09.727 --> 00:21:11.770
- Mm. - Do you know. I sneak out
of this hotel every morning

525
00:21:11.771 --> 00:21:15.273
to avoid running into her dad.
who is. of course. staying here.

526
00:21:15.274 --> 00:21:17.568
eating every single last one
of their bar nuts.

527
00:21:18.903 --> 00:21:20.403
God. that man loves nuts.

528
00:21:20.404 --> 00:21:21.946
Lots of people love nuts.
I love nuts.

529
00:21:21.947 --> 00:21:23.907
God. why is this
happening to me?

530
00:21:23.908 --> 00:21:25.909
Is that rhetorical. or do you want
an actual answer?

531
00:21:25.910 --> 00:21:27.452
I can take it.

532
00:21:27.453 --> 00:21:29.829
I think it's because
some people see you

533
00:21:29.830 --> 00:21:32.290
as a narcissistic asshole
with a punchable face.

534
00:21:32.291 --> 00:21:34.834
- Case in point.
- Do people see me that way?

535
00:21:34.835 --> 00:21:36.127
Some people do.

536
00:21:36.128 --> 00:21:37.963
- Do you see me that way?
- No.

537
00:21:39.632 --> 00:21:40.841
Not all the time.

538
00:21:41.592 --> 00:21:43.426
I mean. you're choosing
to stay at a hotel

539
00:21:43.427 --> 00:21:45.762
instead of my apartment.
and some people

540
00:21:45.763 --> 00:21:48.306
might find that perplexing.

541
00:21:48.307 --> 00:21:50.433
You have a roommate.
and. you know.

542
00:21:50.434 --> 00:21:52.436
moving in is a...
is a big step.

543
00:21:53.103 --> 00:21:54.604
We're having a child together.

544
00:21:54.605 --> 00:21:56.981
Okay. well...
if I'm such a total bastard.

545
00:21:56.982 --> 00:21:58.316
why would you even
wanna be with me?

546
00:21:58.317 --> 00:22:00.860
Well. at first.
mostly your face.

547
00:22:00.861 --> 00:22:03.613
But then. also your mind.
and that accent.

548
00:22:03.614 --> 00:22:06.450
Seriously. it's like having sex
with Paddington Bear.

549
00:22:07.952 --> 00:22:10.203
- And that does it for me.
- Well. a wise bear

550
00:22:10.204 --> 00:22:12.288
always has a marmalade sandwich
underneath his hat.

551
00:22:12.289 --> 00:22:14.666
- What are you talking about?
- It's just what the bear says.

552
00:22:14.667 --> 00:22:16.167
Look. every human
is a mixed bag.

553
00:22:16.168 --> 00:22:18.044
We all have our good qualities
and our terrible ones.

554
00:22:18.045 --> 00:22:20.129
and neuroscience tells us
our brains have plasticity.

555
00:22:20.130 --> 00:22:21.798
That means through repetition
and intention.

556
00:22:21.799 --> 00:22:23.341
we decide
who we're gonna become.

557
00:22:23.342 --> 00:22:25.301
And you?
I think you're at a crossroads.

558
00:22:25.302 --> 00:22:27.303
But I think you
are going to step up

559
00:22:27.304 --> 00:22:29.473
and become the man
I know you're capable of being.

560
00:22:30.474 --> 00:22:33.560
- And what if I don't?
- Well. then I move on.

561
00:22:33.561 --> 00:22:35.937
There. all done.
Anything else?

562
00:22:35.938 --> 00:22:38.064
- A bold lip. perhaps?
- I think I'm good.

563
00:22:38.065 --> 00:22:40.860
Coward.
I'm going back to class.

564
00:22:46.073 --> 00:22:47.740
Oh.

565
00:22:47.741 --> 00:22:48.950
Huh?

566
00:22:50.911 --> 00:22:53.163
- You took it?
- Yeah. I did.

567
00:22:56.208 --> 00:22:58.001
You did the one thing
I never did

568
00:22:58.002 --> 00:22:59.420
to make me feel worse?

569
00:22:59.920 --> 00:23:01.839
Hmm. Okay.

570
00:23:03.841 --> 00:23:05.925
Look. I know you didn't like it

571
00:23:05.926 --> 00:23:08.261
when I called you a rock star.
but you are.

572
00:23:08.262 --> 00:23:09.721
- Please don't.
- You are.

573
00:23:09.722 --> 00:23:11.347
Get over it.

574
00:23:11.348 --> 00:23:13.182
But recently. you have been
doing some stuff

575
00:23:13.183 --> 00:23:15.352
that's a little loser-ish.

576
00:23:15.936 --> 00:23:18.354
I know. because
I have been there.

577
00:23:18.355 --> 00:23:20.189
Lack of game
recognizes lack of game.

578
00:23:20.190 --> 00:23:21.400
Ugh.

579
00:23:22.026 --> 00:23:23.568
Katie. you were right about me.

580
00:23:23.569 --> 00:23:25.446
I didn't bounce back.

581
00:23:26.447 --> 00:23:28.197
And I am not resilient.

582
00:23:28.198 --> 00:23:30.367
And I hope I didn't
pass that down to you.

583
00:23:31.452 --> 00:23:33.370
Come on.
You love this place.

584
00:23:34.204 --> 00:23:37.958
The only thing you need to do to stay
is to be brave.

585
00:23:40.210 --> 00:23:42.879
And to write a letter that says
that you're mentally ill.

586
00:23:42.880 --> 00:23:44.423
- Jesus Christ.
- Ack.

587
00:23:48.260 --> 00:23:49.761
Help me write it.

588
00:23:49.762 --> 00:23:52.555
The Elizabeth Stoddard
Student Center just opened.

589
00:23:52.556 --> 00:23:53.890
You'll notice. right behind you.

590
00:23:53.891 --> 00:23:57.560
we kept the original
brick facade from 1821.

591
00:23:57.561 --> 00:23:59.896
- Cristle said you were here.
- Thank you.

592
00:23:59.897 --> 00:24:01.230
You know.
I hate this damn building.

593
00:24:01.231 --> 00:24:03.191
- Ah.
- They took a classic example

594
00:24:03.192 --> 00:24:06.444
of Neo-Gothic architecture
and slapped a greenhouse on it.

595
00:24:06.445 --> 00:24:08.571
- Well. they also added a smashburger place.
- Exactly.

596
00:24:08.572 --> 00:24:10.782
We're sacrificing
tradition for what?

597
00:24:10.783 --> 00:24:12.075
More fat kids?

598
00:24:12.076 --> 00:24:13.493
We damn sure
got plenty of those.

599
00:24:13.494 --> 00:24:15.078
No. no.
Not out loud.

600
00:24:15.079 --> 00:24:16.913
- Thank you.
- Okay.

601
00:24:16.914 --> 00:24:18.915
What brought all this on?

602
00:24:18.916 --> 00:24:21.084
- Rough dinner with Dean Riggs.
- Mm.

603
00:24:21.085 --> 00:24:22.753
And I had to tell him
we were cutting his budget.

604
00:24:23.504 --> 00:24:26.172
It just feels like this
is my whole job now.

605
00:24:26.173 --> 00:24:27.799
People come
and ask me for things

606
00:24:27.800 --> 00:24:29.926
that they really care about.
I have to say no.

607
00:24:29.927 --> 00:24:31.970
and then they
hold it against me.

608
00:24:31.971 --> 00:24:34.263
Okay. your real friends know
that this comes with the gig.

609
00:24:34.264 --> 00:24:36.475
- We're not gonna hold it against you.
- Hope so.

610
00:24:39.478 --> 00:24:41.479
I have to move
<i>The Ludlow Review</i> online.

611
00:24:41.480 --> 00:24:43.940
It's part of
our Green Initiative.

612
00:24:43.941 --> 00:24:45.692
Every year we print it.
it just winds up

613
00:24:45.693 --> 00:24:48.152
littered all over campus
like a paper factory exploded.

614
00:24:48.153 --> 00:24:49.278
Walt. you can't do that.

615
00:24:49.279 --> 00:24:51.322
So many people
are gonna be upset.

616
00:24:51.323 --> 00:24:54.659
No. The 36 students who get published
will be upset.

617
00:24:54.660 --> 00:24:56.954
Some of their 72 parents. and...

618
00:24:57.955 --> 00:24:58.956
and me.

619
00:25:01.000 --> 00:25:03.794
I read it cover to cover
every year.

620
00:25:07.464 --> 00:25:09.133
I'm really sorry.

621
00:25:12.177 --> 00:25:14.721
"All of that said.
I am truly and profoundly sorry.

622
00:25:14.722 --> 00:25:16.806
My behavior was unhinged.
and I..."

623
00:25:16.807 --> 00:25:19.142
- I don't love "unhinged."
- Really?

624
00:25:19.143 --> 00:25:21.185
I'm gonna use
"overwhelmed."

625
00:25:21.186 --> 00:25:22.688
It's your letter.
Doesn't have to be great.

626
00:25:24.231 --> 00:25:25.732
But I love it.

627
00:25:25.733 --> 00:25:27.483
Okay. done.

628
00:25:27.484 --> 00:25:29.694
- Look at this guy.
- Mm.

629
00:25:29.695 --> 00:25:31.404
- I get to hide him. right?
- All yours.

630
00:25:31.405 --> 00:25:33.990
I'm gonna save it for when
I need a pick-me-up.

631
00:25:33.991 --> 00:25:35.825
Like. first time
I see that fucker

632
00:25:35.826 --> 00:25:37.911
- pushing around a stroller.
- Mm.

633
00:25:39.038 --> 00:25:41.582
Wait. what now?

634
00:25:50.007 --> 00:25:51.841
Hi!
Hi. I'm so sorry.

635
00:25:51.842 --> 00:25:54.635
- I forgot my key again.
- No problem.

636
00:25:54.636 --> 00:25:56.345
That's happening to you a lot.

637
00:25:56.346 --> 00:25:58.223
I know. I'm so mad at myself!

638
00:25:59.349 --> 00:26:00.933
{\an8}<i>How do we expect
the Russian government</i>

639
00:26:00.934 --> 00:26:04.020
{\an8}<i>to respond to this bold move
from Downing Street?</i>

640
00:26:04.021 --> 00:26:05.980
{\an8}<i>Well. it's certainly
not going to go smoothly.</i>

641
00:26:05.981 --> 00:26:07.648
{\an8}<i>that's for sure.</i>

642
00:26:07.649 --> 00:26:09.734
{\an8}<i>- You got her pregnant?!
- No. is that a ladle?</i>

643
00:26:14.406 --> 00:26:15.573
{\an8}<i>Not now!</i>

644
00:26:15.574 --> 00:26:17.200
{\an8}<i>- Mr. Bates...
- It's a big opportunity. Greg!</i>

645
00:26:17.201 --> 00:26:18.701
{\an8}<i>...you're live on the BBC.</i>

646
00:26:18.702 --> 00:26:19.744
{\an8}<i>Ow!</i>

647
00:26:21.789 --> 00:26:24.123
- Is that Greg?
- Yes.

648
00:26:24.124 --> 00:26:25.249
Fuck him up.

649
00:26:27.628 --> 00:26:29.170
- Oh!
- Oh. my God.

650
00:26:29.171 --> 00:26:30.296
- Oh!
- Oh!

651
00:26:31.548 --> 00:26:34.133
Eli! Eli!

652
00:26:34.134 --> 00:26:36.303
Eli. you okay?
You need your inhaler?

653
00:26:48.899 --> 00:26:50.066
<i>Hey there.</i>

654
00:26:50.067 --> 00:26:51.568
You got a coffee walk in you?

655
00:26:52.402 --> 00:26:53.779
Can't. I'm really busy.

656
00:27:00.744 --> 00:27:02.453
- Hey.
- Hey!

657
00:27:02.454 --> 00:27:06.082
I appreciate you putting
all this unfortunate fire business to rest.

658
00:27:06.083 --> 00:27:09.752
Oh. yeah.
No problem at all.

659
00:27:09.753 --> 00:27:11.295
Say. when you were
in the cold plunge.

660
00:27:11.296 --> 00:27:14.132
you didn't happen
to see my gun. did you?

661
00:27:14.133 --> 00:27:15.508
- I did not.
- It's fine.

662
00:27:15.509 --> 00:27:17.344
I probably left it on my dash.

663
00:27:18.345 --> 00:27:20.972
Ah! Oh! No.

664
00:27:20.973 --> 00:27:22.598
I left it at the gun range.

665
00:27:22.599 --> 00:27:24.517
Best place to leave a gun.

666
00:27:24.518 --> 00:27:25.977
They're hard to keep track of.

667
00:27:30.315 --> 00:27:32.151
I thought I'd try
to be less perplexing.

668
00:27:39.158 --> 00:27:40.784
I'm funnier than people think.

669
00:27:41.994 --> 00:27:43.787
Thank you.
Thank you.

670
00:27:44.913 --> 00:27:46.372
Ugh. this fucking guy.

671
00:27:46.373 --> 00:27:48.166
Hello. Mo.
How are you?

672
00:27:48.167 --> 00:27:49.876
What. are you moving in?

673
00:27:52.212 --> 00:27:54.881
Well. thanks for coming
to see me off.

674
00:27:54.882 --> 00:27:55.883
Yeah.

675
00:27:56.967 --> 00:27:59.552
I'm not. like. crushed
that you're leaving.

676
00:27:59.553 --> 00:28:00.970
No offense.

677
00:28:00.971 --> 00:28:03.306
Um. but...

678
00:28:03.307 --> 00:28:04.892
...I am really glad
that you came.

679
00:28:05.893 --> 00:28:07.060
Me. too.

680
00:28:08.478 --> 00:28:10.480
- I love you.
- I love you back.

681
00:28:13.317 --> 00:28:14.359
Bye. Dad.

682
00:28:15.527 --> 00:28:17.154
Bye. sweetie.

683
00:28:18.530 --> 00:28:20.823
- See you Monday!
- Wait. what?

684
00:28:20.824 --> 00:28:22.533
Go. go. go!

685
00:29:25.389 --> 00:29:27.307
<i>Bye-bye.</i>

